1 or more than $1,000 and be imprisoned in the county jail not less than 72 hours or more than 1 year.
2 (iii) Upon a first or second conviction, the offender may be ordered into misdemeanor probation as
3 provided in 46-23-1005.
4 (iv) On a third or subsequent conviction for partner or family member assault, the offender shall be
5 fined not less than $500 and not more than $50,000 and be imprisoned for a term not less than 30 days and not
6 more than 5 years. If the term of imprisonment does not exceed 1 year, the person shall be imprisoned in the
7 county jail. If the term of imprisonment exceeds 1 year, the person shall be imprisoned in the state prison.
8 (v) If the offense was committed within the vision or hearing of a minor, the judge shall consider
9 the minor's presence as a factor at the time of sentencing.
10 (b) For the purpose of determining the number of convictions under this section, a conviction
11 means:
12 (i) a conviction, as defined in 45-2-101, under this section;
13 (ii) a conviction for domestic abuse under this section;
14 (iii) a conviction for a violation of a statute similar to this section in another state;
15 (iv) if the offender was a partner or family member of the victim, a conviction for aggravated assault
16 under 45-5-202 or assault with a weapon under 45-5-213;
17 (v) a conviction for strangulation of a partner or family member under 45-5-215;
18 (vi) a conviction in another state for an offense related to domestic violence between partners or
19 family members, as those terms are defined in this section, regardless of what the offense is named or whether
20 it is misdemeanor or felony, if the offense involves conduct similar to conduct that is prohibited under 45-5-202,
21 45-5-213, or this section; or
22 (vii) a forfeiture of bail or collateral deposited to secure the defendant's appearance in court in this
23 state or in another state for a violation of a statute similar to this section, which forfeiture has not been vacated.
24 (4) (a) An offender convicted of partner or family member assault is required to pay for and
25 complete a counseling assessment with a focus on violence, controlling behavior, dangerousness, and
26 chemical dependency. An investigative criminal justice report, as defined in 45-5-231, must be copied and sent
27 to the offender intervention program, as defined in 45-5-231, to assist the counseling provider in properly
28 assessing the offender's need for counseling and treatment. Counseling providers shall take all required
