1 precautions to ensure the confidentiality of the report. If the report contains confidential information relating to
2 the victim's location or not related to the charged offense, that information must be deleted from the report prior
3 to being sent to the offender intervention program.
4 (b) The offender shall complete all recommendations for counseling, referrals, attendance at
5 psychoeducational groups, or treatment, including any indicated chemical dependency treatment, made by the
6 counseling provider. The counseling provider must be approved by the court or the department of corrections.
7 The counseling must include a preliminary assessment for counseling, as defined in 45-5-231. The offender
8 shall complete a minimum of 40 hours of counseling. The counseling may include attendance at
9 psychoeducational groups, as defined in 45-5-231, in addition to the assessment. The preliminary assessment
10 and counseling that holds the offender accountable for the offender's violent or controlling behavior must meet
11 the standards established pursuant to 44-7-210 and be:
12 (i) with a person licensed under Title 37, chapter 17, 22, or 23;
13 (ii) with a professional person as defined in 53-21-102; or
14 (iii) in a specialized domestic violence intervention program.
15 (c) The minimum counseling and attendance at psychoeducational groups provided in subsection
16 (4)(b) must be directed to the violent or controlling conduct of the offender. Other issues indicated by the
17 assessment may be addressed in additional counseling beyond the minimum 40 hours. Subsection (4)(b) does
18 not prohibit the placement of the offender in other appropriate treatment if the court determines that there is no
19 available treatment program directed to the violent or controlling conduct of the offender.
20 (5) In addition to any sentence imposed under subsections (3) and (4), after determining the
21 financial resources and future ability of the offender to pay restitution as provided for in 46-18-242, the court
22 shall require the offender, if able, to pay the victim's reasonable actual medical, housing, wage loss, and
23 counseling costs.
24 (6) In addition to the requirements of subsection (5), if financially able, the offender must be
25 ordered to pay for the costs of the offender's probation, if probation is ordered by the court.
26 (7) The court may prohibit an offender convicted under this section from possession or use of the
27 firearm used in the assault. The court may enforce 45-8-323 if a firearm was used in the assault.
28 (8) The court shall provide an offender with a written copy of the offender's sentence at the time of
